cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating depth from a single RGB image using deep learning methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper proposes a novel set loss over multiple images, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of deep learning methods for estimating depth also suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also mentions 3D projections, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the use of a two-streamed CNN suggests that it may belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category, as this type of network is often used in robotics applications.
